#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:166
msgid "Changes to how ROS 2 and Gazebo integrate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:168
msgid ""
"Starting with Jazzy Jalisco, we are streamlining how ROS 2 and `Gazebo "
"<https://gazebosim.org>`__ integrate. For every ROS 2 release, there will be "
"a recommended, supported Gazebo release that goes along with that release. "
"For Jazzy Jalisco, the recommended Gazebo release will be Harmonic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:172
msgid ""
"To make it easier for ROS 2 packages to consume Gazebo packages, there are "
"now ``gz_*_vendor`` packages. Those packages are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:175
msgid "gz_common_vendor: https://github.com/gazebo-release/gz_common_vendor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:176
msgid "gz_cmake_vendor: https://github.com/gazebo-release/gz_cmake_vendor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:177
msgid "gz_math_vendor: https://github.com/gazebo-release/gz_math_vendor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:178
msgid ""
"gz_transport_vendor: https://github.com/gazebo-release/gz_transport_vendor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:179
msgid "gz_sensor_vendor: https://github.com/gazebo-release/gz_sensor_vendor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:180
msgid "gz_sim_vendor: https://github.com/gazebo-release/gz_sim_vendor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:181
msgid "gz_tools_vendor: https://github.com/gazebo-release/gz_tools_vendor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:182
msgid "gz_utils_vendor: https://github.com/gazebo-release/gz_utils_vendor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:183
msgid "sdformat_vendor: https://github.com/gazebo-release/sdformat_vendor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:185
msgid ""
"ROS 2 packages can use the functionality in these packages by adding "
"dependencies in ``package.xml``, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:187
msgid "<depend>gz_math_vendor</depend>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:191
msgid "And then using them in ``CMakeLists.txt``, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:193
msgid ""
"find_package(gz_math_vendor REQUIRED)\n"
"find_package(gz-math)\n"
"\n"
"add_executable(my_executable src/exe.cpp)\n"
"target_link_libraries(my_executable gz-math::core)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Releases/Release-Jazzy-Jalisco.rst:203
msgid ""
"It will still be possible to use alternate Gazebo versions with Jazzy "
"Jalisco.  But those will not be as well tested or integrated with ROS 2.  "
"See https://gazebosim.org/docs/harmonic/ros_installation for more "
"information."
msgstr ""

